## Habitat [/single_habitat_data]

###  /single_habitatl_data/?q=HABITAT [GET]

Retrieves data for a given habitat: name, suitability status, associated animals/threats.

Example: Let's say you want to find data on "Forest-Temperate."
    
**HTTP Request:**
`http://docs.endangeredanimals.apiary.io/single_habitatl_data/?q=Forest-Temperate`

+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Body
    
            {
                "name": "Forest - Temperate",
                "suitability_status": "suitable",
                "assoc_animals": [
                    "African Elephant",
                    "Kangaroo"
                ],
                "assoc_threats": [
                    "Housing and urban areas", 
                    "Droughts"
                 ]
            }

